Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Write os-independent code for easy portability between different systems and architectures.
 libosal is an operating system abstraction layer Library. It's purpose is to write os-independent code for easy portability between different systems and architectures. It contains of 'binary semaphores', 'condition variables', 'io', 'message queues', 'mutex', 'semaphores', 'shared memory', 'spinlocks', 'tasks', 'timers' and 'traces'.
